The White House Press Secretary has released a statement expressing confidence and support for Ambassador Robert Ford as he returns to Syria. The statement emphasizes the United States' solidarity with the Syrian people and highlights the importance of Ford's efforts to engage with Syrians in achieving a peaceful and democratic transition. The United States hopes that Ford's presence in the country will send a message of solidarity to the Syrian people. The statement also calls on the Syrian government to fulfill its obligations to protect diplomatic personnel and facilities and allow foreign service officers to conduct their work without intimidation or obstacles.